Class NotificationService

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2

    public class NotificationService
extends android.app.IntentService
    This class provides an interface used to enable the receiving of MoBack Push Notifications. Currently, your project must add in the Google Play Services library to be able to correctly register to receive notifications. Registration with MoBack, to receive a notification, requires a user to be logged in.

      • setNotificationCallback

        public static boolean setNotificationCallback(Class callback)
        This sets the context and class to open when a notification is pressed. This automatically enables receiving of push alerts.
        Parameters:
        callback - The Class to send an Intent to when the notification is tapped.
        Returns:
        True iff this device supports GCM. False otherwise, even if it need only be downloaded (must be implemented by end developer).

      • setNotificationCallback

        public static boolean setNotificationCallback(Class callback,
                              BasicCompletionBlock completion)
        This sets the context and class to open when a notification is pressed. This automatically enables receiving of push alerts.
        Parameters:
        callback - The Class to send an Intent to when the notification is tapped.
        completion - The callback to use when the push notification registration is complete. No error if null.
        Returns:
        True iff this device supports GCM. False otherwise, even if it need only be downloaded (must be implemented by end developer).
